title: Measurements of Activation Cross Sections of Ta, W for 14 Mev Neutrons

x4freetext: .MEASUREMENTS OF ACTIVATION CROSS SECTIONS OF TA, W

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Japanese report to the I.N.D.C., No.163/L, p.277 (1992)

x4freetext: ARE GIVEN.  PROCEEDINGS OF THE 1992 SYMPOSIUM ON
THE D-BEAM ENERGY WAS 300 KEV AND THE INTENSITY
WAS 5 MILLIAMPS. A SAMPLE TRANSPORT SYSTEM OF SIX
PNEUMATIC TUBES AT ANGLES OF 0, 50, 75, 105, 125 AND
155 DEG TO THE DEUTERON BEAM PROVIDED IRRADIATION
MEV. ANOTHER TUBE WAS PUT AT -105 DEG TO CHECK THE
SYMMETRY OF THE SYSTEM. THE IRRADIATION POSITIONS WERE
ABOUT 15 CM FROM THE TRITIUM TARGET. AN ADDITIONAL
TUBE SET AT -22.5 DEG AND AT 1.5 CM DISTANCE WAS USED
WHEN STRONG ACTIVITIES WERE REQUIRED. THE TRANSFER
TIME WAS ABOUT 2 SEC. THE EFFECTIVE REACTION NEUTRON
ENERGY AT EACH POSITION WAS DETERMINED BY THE RATIO OF
UNCERTAINTY IN THE NEUTRON ENERGY IS ESTIMATED TO BE
EFFECTIVE NEUTRON ENERGY DETERMINED BY ZR/NB METHOD
THREE GE-DETECTORS - 12 PC, 21 PC, 16 PC AT AN
.TWO NIOBIUM FOILS 99.9 PC PURITY, 1*1 CM AREA, 0.1 MM
THICKNESS. ALUMINIUM FOIL PORITY 99,2 PC, 1*1 CM2 AREA
TRUE COINCIDENCE SUM - LESS THAN 0.5 PC
RANDOM COINCIDENCE SUM - LESS THAN 0.4 PC
SAMPLE THICKNESS - 0.2-0.6 PC (20 PC OF CORRECTIONS)
DATA ARE TAKEN FROM TABLE 3 OF THE
TOTAL ERROR EQUAL TO QUADRATIC SUM OF
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY ERROR FOR E-GAMMA LESS
DELTA-E IS QUADRATIC SUM OF ERRORS ERR-S THROUGH ERR-8
DELTA-R IS QUADRATIC SUM OF ERRS ERR-9 THROUGH ERR-13
isotope at SUBENT 006 was changed on 73-TA-182-M2
